      "content": "A solid red light on your router's internet indicator usually means your device is not successfully communicating with your Internet Service Provider (ISP). You should first check if your ISP is having a localized outage by visiting their status page or calling their support line. Next, unplug the power cable from your router, wait about 30 seconds, and then plug it back in to force a restart. If the light remains red after this reset, you may need to reinsert your modem or coaxial cable into the back of the router, or contact your internet provider for repair.",
