      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried the power cycle thing but a red light came back after like 2 mins. and i checked the cables, they seem tight. is there anything else i can try before i spend an hour on hold with the provider? maybe some settings i can change on the router itself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you can try resetting the router's DHCP settings within its administration panel to clear any IP address conflicts. Additionally, switching your wireless protocol from 5GHz to 2.4GHz might help if devices are struggling to connect through that band. However, if the light persists after these changes, the issue might persist on the ISP's network side even after a refresh. It is generally better to reconfigure your router's security and DNS settings rather than spending too much time troubleshooting before contacting support.",
      "source": "target",
